This paper discusses the efficient querying of XML data, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB). It also focuses on tree patterns, which are graphic representations of queries over data trees, and their optimization (cs.IR, cs.DS). The paper also discusses actual tree pattern-based developments, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper is a comprehensive survey of a significant research topic, which could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
